# Public Arena Discovery / Listing Feature

Add a public discovery surface so visitors can browse recently published arenas without needing a direct link. Clicking a listed arena opens the existing `/p/:slug` read-only page.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Schema migration needed.** Three new columns (`title`, `contestant_count`, `round_count`) must be added to the existing `published_arenas` table in Supabase. This is a **manual SQL migration** — I will provide the exact SQL, but you must run it in the Supabase dashboard before the feature works.

> [!NOTE]
> Previously published arenas (before this migration) will have `NULL` values for the new columns. The listing UI will handle these gracefully by showing fallback text.

---

## Proposed Changes

### Supabase Schema

#### SQL migration (run manually in Supabase SQL editor):

```sql
ALTER TABLE published_arenas
  ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS title text NOT NULL DEFAULT '',
  ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS contestant_count integer NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,
  ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS round_count integer NOT NULL DEFAULT 0;
```

---

### API Layer

#### [MODIFY] [publish.ts](file:///c:/Users/Batzatar/Desktop/Rankmine%20Arena/src/api/publish.ts)

1. **Update [publishArena()](file:///c:/Users/Batzatar/Desktop/Rankmine%20Arena/src/api/publish.ts#6-18)** — insert `title`, `contestant_count`, and `round_count` alongside `slug` and `payload`. Extract these from the payload argument.

2. **Add `PublishedArenaListItem` type** — lightweight type for listing cards (no full payload):
   - `slug`, `title`, `created_at`, `contestant_count`, `round_count`

3. **Add `fetchRecentPublishedArenas(limit?: number)`** — queries `published_arenas` ordered by `created_at desc`, selecting only listing-card fields (no `payload`). Default limit: 12.

